Tianwei Sichuan Silicon Co. , a
Chinese maker of polysilicon, failed to repay 145 million  yuan 
($23.6 million) owed to the Chengdu branch of the Export-Import
Bank of  China  due on May 31.  The company has to pay an additional 120 million yuan in
the outstanding principal due Nov. 30, Tianweiâ€™s stakeholder,
Sichuan Minjiang Hydropower Co., said in a  filing  to the
Shanghai stock exchange. Minjiang Hydropower has a 14 percent
stake in Tianwei Silicon.  Tianwei Sichuan suspended production in 2011, Minjiang said
in a Dec. 15, 2011 filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
